de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.parsedMetadata

Class VirtuosoMetadata

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.parsedMetadata.ParsedMetadata
      • de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.parsedMetadata.VirtuosoMetadata

  • public class VirtuosoMetadata
extends ParsedMetadata
    This class extends the abstract class ParsedMetadata. It searches in the Virtuoso Triple Store for a given URI and parses all relevant information concerning this URI in the systems data classes.
    Since:
    01.11.2013
    Author:
    Sebastian Schulz
    See Also:
    parseMetadata(), executeQuery(), prepareQuery(), processSolution(QuerySolution), eliminatePandaPrefix(RDFNode), processOperationalMetadata(String, String), processAdministrativeMetadata(String, String), processArealMetadata(String, String), processTemporalMetadata(String, String), processTypeMetadata(String, String)

    • Method Detail

      • parseMetadata

        public void parseMetadata()
                   throws MetadataNotFoundException,
                          ProcessingUriException
        This overridden method calls the executeQuery() method and iterates over the returned ResultSet to process the single rows with calling the processSolution(QuerySolution) method. If the ResultSet has no entries, a Exception is thrown.
        Specified by:
        parseMetadata in class ParsedMetadata
        Throws:
        MetadataNotFoundException - if there are no results for the given URI
        ProcessingUriException - if there was a problem while processing the single objects

      • executeQuery

        private com.hp.hpl.jena.query.ResultSet executeQuery()
        This method calls the prepareQuery() method to get the query string. Then it manages the query execution and returns its results.
        Returns:
        a ResultSet which holds the queries results.

      • prepareQuery

        private java.lang.String prepareQuery()
        This method builds the actual query string which is responsible to get all the RDF predicates and objects for the given URI from the graph with virtuosoGraphName which is saved on the Virtuoso server.
        Returns:
        queryString

      • processSolution

        private void processSolution(com.hp.hpl.jena.query.QuerySolution solution)
                      throws ProcessingUriException
        This method filters the MetadataType of the predicate and calls the a further process method according to its type. If the predicate isn't listed in the RDFInputs predicate hash map, nothing is processed.
        Parameters:
        solution - - The QuerySoultion object which represents the current "row" in the queries result set.
        Throws:
        ProcessingUriException

      • eliminatePandaPrefix

        private java.lang.String eliminatePandaPrefix(com.hp.hpl.jena.rdf.model.RDFNode solutionNode)
        This method trims the RDFNode name and returns a string with the node name without it's panda prefix.
        Parameters:
        solutionNode - - The RDFNode object from the solution (e.g. "?p" or "?o" node)
        Returns:
        a String with the node name without panda prefix

      • processOperationalMetadata

        private void processOperationalMetadata(java.lang.String predicate,
                              java.lang.String object)
                                 throws javax.management.modelmbean.XMLParseException
        This method is called if a operational metadata entry has been detected, it adds the object's value as an Operation to the Operations object of the current ParsedMetadata object.
        Parameters:
        predicate - - the predicate as a string
        object - - the object value as a string
        Throws:
        javax.management.modelmbean.XMLParseException - in case the operational timestamp has a wrong format
